Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Hooda, out Stumped!! If Bairstow hasn't messed it up, Hooda should be out stumped. Ball fell out of his gloves at some point. Nah, he's done alright. It was in his fingertips when he broke the stumps. Kings XI are unraveling here. It's a leg-break at pace. Hooda is stretching forward to get close to the pitch of it, but he's nowhere close. And all he does is drag his back foot out as well, while the ball spins past the edge. Also looks like he is playing for the googly. Bairstow has it under control for long enough to send him packing. Hooda st Bairstow b Rashid Khan 0(2)

Commentary Text: Holder to Gayle, out Caught by Warner!! He's walked right into Hyderabad's trap. They've resorted to death-bowling inside the first ten to Gayle, keeping him quiet with yorker after yorker. So that one rare time when Holder floats it slow, and wide to draw out a drive, Gayle gets foxed. He slices, flat, without timing, without elevation, and Warner's right there waiting for exactly this at long-off. Oh, and he's pumped, it's Gayle after all. Gayle c Warner b Holder 20(20) [4s-2 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Jordan to Shankar, FOUR, never overpitch within the sticks to this guy. Long hands, those high elbows help him make great contact on the straight-batted hits.
